<i>adverb</i>: 혹여 [호겨], 혹시 [혹씨], 혹 [혹], 어쩜 [어쩜], 어쩌면 [어쩌면], 아마도 [아마도], 아마 [아마], 또 [또] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>혹여 [호겨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. by any chance</dd><br>
<dd>그러할 리는 없지만 만약에.</dd><br>
<dd>Not probably but possibly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. accidentally</dd><br>
<dd>어쩌다가 우연히.</dd><br>
<dd>By chance.</dd><br>
<dd>3. maybe</dd><br>
<dd>짐작대로 어쩌면.</dd><br>
<dd>Perhaps as one has guessed.</dd><br>
<dt>혹시 [혹씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. by any chance</dd><br>
<dd>그러할 리는 없지만 만약에.</dd><br>
<dd>Not probably but possibly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. accidentally</dd><br>
<dd>어쩌다가 우연히.</dd><br>
<dd>By chance.</dd><br>
<dd>3. maybe</dd><br>
<dd>짐작대로 어쩌면.</dd><br>
<dd>Perhaps as one has guessed.</dd><br>
<dd>4. by any chance</dd><br>
<dd>그러리라 생각하지만 분명하지 않아 말하기를 망설일 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The word that is used when one is hesitant to say something he/she thinks is possible but he/she is uncertain about.</dd><br>
<dt>혹 [혹]</dt><br>
<dd>1. by any chance</dd><br>
<dd>그러할 리는 없지만 만일에.</dd><br>
<dd>Not probably but possibly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. accidentally</dd><br>
<dd>어쩌다가 우연히.</dd><br>
<dd>By chance.</dd><br>
<dd>3. maybe</dd><br>
<dd>짐작대로 어쩌면.</dd><br>
<dd>Perhaps as one has guessed.</dd><br>
<dd>4. sometimes; occasionally; once in a while</dd><br>
<dd>어쩌다가 아주 가끔.</dd><br>
<dd>Sometimes at random intervals.</dd><br>
<dt>어쩜 [어쩜]</dt><br>
<dd>1. maybe; perhaps; possibly</dd><br>
<dd>확실하지는 않지만 짐작하건대.</dd><br>
<dd>Not sure but presumably.</dd><br>
<dd>2. how; what</dd><br>
<dd>도대체 어떻게 해서.</dd><br>
<dd>How on earth, as if one cannot believe it.</dd><br>
<dt>어쩌면 [어쩌면]</dt><br>
<dd>1. maybe; perhaps; possibly</dd><br>
<dd>확실하지는 않지만 짐작하건대.</dd><br>
<dd>Not sure but presumably.</dd><br>
<dd>2. how; what</dd><br>
<dd>도대체 어떻게 해서.</dd><br>
<dd>How on earth.</dd><br>
<dt>아마도 [아마도]</dt><br>
<dd>maybe; likely</dd><br>
<dd>(강조하는 말로) 아마.</dd><br>
<dd>(emphasizing form) Probably.</dd><br>
<dt>아마 [아마]</dt><br>
<dd>maybe; likely</dd><br>
<dd>확실하게 말할 수는 없지만 짐작하거나 생각해 볼 때 그럴 가능성이 크게.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to indicate that something is possible but not sure or certain.</dd><br>
<dt>또 [또]</dt><br>
<dd>1. once more</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 행동이 다시.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of happening or behaving again.</dd><br>
<dd>2. moreover; besides</dd><br>
<dd>그 밖에 더.</dd><br>
<dd>In addition to that.</dd><br>
<dd>3. nevertheless</dd><br>
<dd>그럼에도 불구하고.</dd><br>
<dd>Although.</dd><br>
<dd>4. maybe</dd><br>
<dd>그래도 혹시.</dd><br>
<dd>But possibly.</dd><br>
<dd>5. and; as well</dd><br>
<dd>그뿐만 아니라.</dd><br>
<dd>Not only that.</dd><br>
<dd>6. and</dd><br>
<dd>단어를 이어 줄 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used when connecting words.</dd><br>
<dd>7. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>놀람이나 안도의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to indicate one's surprise or relief.</dd><br>
<dd>8. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>앞에 있는 말이 뜻하는 내용을 부정하거나 이상하게 여길 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used when denying the preceding statement or considering it strange.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>